Ceratodon purpureus.label: Ceratodon purpureus
Ceratodon purpureus.description: Ceratodon purpureus is a dioicous moss with a color ranging from yellow-green to red. The height amounts to 3 centimeters. It is found worldwide, mainly in urban areas and next to roads on dry sand soils. Wikipedia

Dicranales.label: Dicranales
Dicranales.description: Dicranales is an order of mosses in the subclass Dicranidae. Wikipedia

Grimmiales.label: Grimmiales
Grimmiales.description: Grimmiales is an order of mosses in the subclass Dicranidae. Wikipedia

Hypnaceae.label: Hypnaceae
Hypnaceae.description: Hypnaceae is a large family of moss with broad worldwide occurrence in the class Bryopsida, subclass Bryidae and order Hypnales. Genera include Hypnum and Ptilium. Wikipedia

Java moss.label: Java moss
Java moss.description: Java moss is a moss belonging to the Hypnaceae family. Native to Southeast Asia, it is commonly used in freshwater aquariums. It attaches to rocks, roots, and driftwood. Wikipedia

Polytrichaceae.label: Polytrichaceae
Polytrichaceae.description: The Polytrichaceae is a common family of mosses. Members of this family tend to be larger than other mosses with a thickened central stem and a rhizome. The leaves have a midrib that bears lamellae on the upper surface. Wikipedia

Sphagnaceae.label: Sphagnaceae
Sphagnaceae.description: The Sphagnaceae is a family of moss with only one living genus Sphagnum. Wikipedia

Bryopsida.label: Bryopsida
Bryopsida.description: The Bryopsida constitute the largest class of mosses, containing 95% of all moss species. It consists of approximately 11,500 species, common throughout the whole world. Wikipedia

Hylocomium splendens.label: Hylocomium splendens
Hylocomium splendens.description: Hylocomium splendens, commonly known as Glittering Wood-moss, Stairstep Moss and Mountain Fern Moss, is a perennial clonal moss with a widespread distribution in Northern Hemisphere boreal forests. Wikipedia

Physcomitrella patens.label: Physcomitrella patens
Physcomitrella patens.description: Physcomitrella patens is a moss used as a model organism for studies on plant evolution, development and physiology. Wikipedia

Polytrichum.label: Polytrichum
Polytrichum.description:
Polytrichum is a genus of mosses — commonly called haircap moss or hair moss — which contains approximately 70 species that cover a cosmopolitan distribution.
The Polythrichum genus has a number of closely related sporophytic characters. Wikipedia

Polytrichum commune.label: Polytrichum commune
Polytrichum commune.description: Polytrichum commune is a species of moss found in many regions with high humidity and rainfall. The species can be exceptionally tall for a moss with stems often exceeding 30 cm though rarely reaching ... Wikipedia

Ptilium crista-castrensis.label: Ptilium crista-castrensis
Ptilium crista-castrensis.description: Ptilium crista-castrensis is a moss species within the family Hypnaceae, in the class Bryopsida, subclass Bryidae and order Hypnales. Wikipedia

Sphagnum girgensohnii.label: Sphagnum girgensohnii
Sphagnum girgensohnii.description:
Common green peat moss is a species of peat moss with a Holarctic and Indo-Malesian distribution.
Lake Superior Provincial Park Wikipedia

Sphagnum magellanicum.label: Sphagnum magellanicum
Sphagnum magellanicum.description: Sphagnum magellanicum is a widespread species of moss found in wet places throughout boreal forests of North America, South America and Eurasia. It has a distinctive reddish-purple color which usually makes it easy to recognize. Wikipedia

Ambuchanania.label: Ambuchanania
Ambuchanania.description: Ambuchanania leucobryoides is the only species of genus Ambuchanania. It is a Sphagnum-like moss endemic to Tasmania. Wikipedia

Aneuraceae.label: Aneuraceae
Aneuraceae.description: Aneuraceae is a family of thallose liverworts in the order Metzgeriales. Most species are very small with narrow, branching thalli. Wikipedia

Aulacomnium palustre.label: Aulacomnium palustre
Aulacomnium palustre.description: Aulacomnium palustre is a moss that is nearly cosmopolitan in distribution. It occurs in North America, the Dominican Republic, Venezuela, Eurasia, and New Zealand. Wikipedia

Flabellidium spinosum.label: Flabellidium spinosum
Flabellidium spinosum.description: Flabellidium spinosum was a species of moss in the Brachytheciaceae family. It was endemic to Bolivia. It is also known as the Santa Cruz Bryophyte. Wikipedia

Funaria hygrometrica.label: Funaria hygrometrica
Funaria hygrometrica.description:
Funaria hygrometrica is a common type of water moss which grows on moist, shady, and damp soil. It can also be found on moist walls and the crevices of rocks and places where recent fires have taken place.
The plant body is green, soft, and upright. Wikipedia

Funariales.label: Funariales
Funariales.description: Funariales is an order of mosses. Wikipedia

Lepidoziaceae.label: Lepidoziaceae
Lepidoziaceae.description:
A family of leafy liverworts. It is a group of small plants that are widely distributed.
Most of the species of this family are found in tropical regions.
The main characteristics of the family
1. Oil bodies are small and unsegmented.
2. Wikipedia

Lunularia.label: Lunularia
Lunularia.description: Lunularia cruciata or crescent-cup liverwort is a liverwort of order Marchantiales, and the only species in the genus Lunularia and family Lunulariaceae. The name refers to the moon-shaped cups, from Latin luna, moon. Wikipedia

Metzgeria.label: Metzgeria
Metzgeria.description: Metzgeria is a genus of thalloid liverworts in the family Metzgeriaceae. The genus was named in honor of Johann Metzger, German copper engraver and art restorer from Staufen, Breisgau, a friend of Raddi ... Wikipedia

Ptilidium.label: Ptilidium
Ptilidium.description: Ptilidium is a genus of liverwort, and is the only genus in family Ptilidiaceae. It includes only three species Ptilidium californicum, Ptilidium ciliare, and Ptilidium pulcherrimum. Wikipedia

Ricciaceae.label: Ricciaceae
Ricciaceae.description:
Ricciaceae is a family of liverworts in order Marchantiales, with two genera.
Riccia
Ricciocarpos Wikipedia

Schistostega.label: Schistostega
Schistostega.description: Schistostega pennata, also called goblin's gold or luminous moss or luminescent moss, is a moss known for its glowing appearance in dark places. It is the only member of the family Schistostegaceae. Wikipedia

Sphagnum affine.label: Sphagnum affine
Sphagnum affine.description: Sphagnum affine is a species of peat moss or sphagnum moss which is exploited to make commercial peat products. This moss has a yellowish coloring. Wikipedia

Sphagnum angustifolium.label: Sphagnum angustifolium
Sphagnum angustifolium.description: Sphagnum angustifolium is a species of peat moss with a Holarctic distribution. Wikipedia

Frullania dilatata.label: Frullania dilatata
Frullania dilatata.description:
Frullania dilatata is a species of liverwort in the Jubulaceae family.
It is found in Ireland, Germany, ... Wikipedia

Ambuchanania leucobryoides.label: Ambuchanania leucobryoides
Ambuchanania leucobryoides.description: Ambuchanania leucobryoides, formerly Sphagnum leucobryoides, is a species of plant in the Sphagnaceae family. It is endemic to Tasmania, Australia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Bruchia bolanderi.label: Bruchia bolanderi
Bruchia bolanderi.description: Bruchia bolanderi is a rare plant of the Western U.S. Oregon, California, and Nevada. It grows on very damp bare soil. One may distinguish it from other mosses by the capsules, which are shaped like little upside-down pear fruits. Wikipedia

Calymperastrum.label: Calymperastrum
Calymperastrum.description: Calymperastrum latifolium is the sole species in the monotypic moss genus Calymperastrum. It is a poorly known moss, having been collected only three times. Wikipedia

Fissidentaceae.label: Fissidentaceae
Fissidentaceae.description: Fissidentaceae is a family of mosses in the order Dicranales. Wikipedia

Fissidentales.label: Fissidentales
Fissidentales.description: Fissidentales is a formerly recognized order of mosses. The family Fissidentaceae is now placed in the order Dicranales. Wikipedia

Hygrohypnum styriacum.label: Hygrohypnum styriacum
Hygrohypnum styriacum.description:
Hygrohypnum styriacum, commonly known as Snow Brook-moss or Hygrohypnum Moss is a species of moss found in the Northern Hemisphere.
It is present in Greenland Iceland, Norway, Poland, Slovakia, Sweden and Scotland. Wikipedia

Jamesoniella.label: Jamesoniella
Jamesoniella.description:
Jamesoniella is a genus of liverwort in family Jamesoniellaceae. It contains the following species
Jamesoniella colorata, Schiffn.
Jamesoniella undulifolia, K. Muell. Wikipedia

Marsupella arctica.label: Marsupella arctica
Marsupella arctica.description: Marsupella arctica, commonly known as Arctic rustwort, is a species of liverwort found in the Northern Hemisphere. It is present in Alaska and Greenland and has a European distribution confined to Scotland and Svalbard. Wikipedia

Neosharpiella.label: Neosharpiella
Neosharpiella.description: Neosharpiella is a genus of moss containing two species in the family Bartramiaceae. The type species Neosharpiella aztecorum grows in alpine regions of central Mexico, while the other species Neosharpiella ... Wikipedia

Takakia lepidozioides.label: Takakia lepidozioides
Takakia lepidozioides.description: Takakia lepidozioides is a species of moss in the Takakiaceae family, one of two species of Takakia. Wikipedia

Tayloria lingulata.label: Tayloria lingulata
Tayloria lingulata.description: Tayloria lingulata, commonly known as Tongue-leaved Gland Moss, Lingulate Dung Moss, or Marsh Collar-moss is a moss found in montane habitats in the Northern Hemisphere including Europe, Asia and North America. Wikipedia

Thamnobryum.label: Thamnobryum
Thamnobryum.description:
Thamnobryum is a genus of moss in family Neckeraceae. It contains the following species
Thamnobryum angustifolium, Crundw.
Thamnobryum fernandesii, Ochyra Wikipedia

Mizutania.label: Mizutania
Mizutania.description: Mizutania is a genus of liverworts restricted to tropical Asia, and contains a single species Mizutania riccardioides. It is classified in order Metzgeriales and is the only member of the family Mizutaniaceae within that order. Wikipedia

Frullania asagrayana.label: Frullania asagrayana
Frullania asagrayana.description: Frullania asagrayana is a reddish-brown species of liverwort in the Jubulaceae family that grows in eastern North America. Wikipedia

Plagiochila deltoidea.label: Plagiochila deltoidea
Plagiochila deltoidea.description: Plagiochila deltoidea is a liverwort that resides on wet ground. It can grow to lengths of up to 60 mm with 3 mm wide leaves. Wikipedia

Andreaea.label: Andreaea
Andreaea.description:
Andreaea is a genus of rock mosses with about 45 species.
They are small, delicate acrocarpous mosses that form dark brown or reddish cushions on wet siliceous rocks in mountainous areas. Wikipedia

Bazzania.label: Bazzania
Bazzania.description:
Bazzania is a genus of liverwort in the family Lepidoziaceae. It contains the following species
Bazzania bhutanica, N. Kitag. & Grolle
Bazzania flaccida Grolle
Bazzania tricrenata Lindb.
Bazzania trilobata Gray Wikipedia

Bryaceae.label: Bryaceae
Bryaceae.description:
Bryaceae is a family of mosses.
Genera include
Acidodontium
Anomobryum
Brachymenium
Bryum
Leptostomopsis
Mniobryoides
Osculatia
Perssonia
Plagiobryum
Ptychostomum
Rhodobryum
Roellia
Rosulabryum Wikipedia

Jamesoniella undulifolia.label: Jamesoniella undulifolia
Jamesoniella undulifolia.description: Jamesoniella undulifolia is a species of liverwort in the Jungermanniaceae family. It is found in Austria, China, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greenland, North Korea, Norway, ... Wikipedia

Physcomitrium pyriforme.label: Physcomitrium pyriforme
Physcomitrium pyriforme.description: Physcomitrium pyriforme, commonly known as common bladder moss, is a bryophyte native to all continents except South America and Antarctica. Its capsules mature beginning in late fall and through the spring. Wikipedia

Pleurozium schreberi.label: Pleurozium schreberi
Pleurozium schreberi.description: Pleurozium schreberi is a moss with a loose growth pattern. The root name pleuro comes from the Latin for ribs, possibly describing how the parts branch from the stem. Wikipedia

Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus.label: Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus
Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus.description: Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus is a species of moss known as springy turf-moss in the United Kingdom, and square goose neck moss in the United States. It is widespread in Eurasia and North America, and has been introduced to the Southern Hemisphere. Wikipedia

Rhytidiadelphus triquetrus.label: Rhytidiadelphus triquetrus
Rhytidiadelphus triquetrus.description: Shaggy moss, Rhytidiadelphus triquetrus, is species of moss in the family Hylocomiaceae. It is often the dominating moss species in moderately rich forest habitats in the boreal regions. Wikipedia

Riccardia chamedryfolia.label: Riccardia chamedryfolia
Riccardia chamedryfolia.description: Riccardia chamedryfolia is a species of liverwort is a terrestrial plant which has been adapted by aquarist as an ornamental plant for the freshwater planted aquarium hobby. Wikipedia

Scapania.label: Scapania
Scapania.description:
Scapania is a genus of plant in Scapaniaceae, a family of liverworts. It contains the following species
Scapania aequiloba Dumort. Wikipedia

Sphaerocarpales.label: Sphaerocarpales
Sphaerocarpales.description: Sphaerocarpales is an order of plants within the liverworts. Approximately twenty species are in this order which is sub-divided into three families Sphaerocarpaceae and Riellaceae, as well as the extinct family Naiaditaceae. Wikipedia

Jensenia.label: Jensenia
Jensenia.description: Jensenia is a bryophyte plant genus in the liverwort family Pallaviciniaceae. It has been treated as a subgenus of Pallavicinia by several authors, though a set of features seems to set it apart as a genus. Wikipedia

Pellia epiphylla.label: Pellia epiphylla
Pellia epiphylla.description: Pellia epiphylla is a species of thallose liverwort. It occurs in North America, Europe, North Africa and parts of Asia. It grows in patches in damp, sheltered places on neutral or acidic substrates. Wikipedia

Ambuchananiaceae.label: Ambuchananiaceae
Ambuchananiaceae.description: Ambuchananiaceae is a family of moss in the order Sphagnales with only two genera, Ambuchanania and Eosphagnum Wikipedia

Bryoerythrophyllum caledonicum.label: Bryoerythrophyllum caledonicum
Bryoerythrophyllum caledonicum.description: Bryoerythrophyllum caledonicum, commonly known as Scottish Beard-moss, is a moss endemic to Scotland. Recognised as a distinct species in 1982, it had been collected occasionally from 1891 onwards under other names. Wikipedia

Colura zoophaga.label: Colura zoophaga
Colura zoophaga.description: Colura zoophaga is a species of epiphytic liverwort that is endemic to the African highlands, specifically parts of Kenya. It belongs to the genus Colura, which has been hypothesized to be carnivorous as early as 1893. Wikipedia

Costesia.label: Costesia
Costesia.description: Costesia is a genus of moss in the family Gigaspermaceae. The genus contains a single species Costesia spongiosa known only from South America, Wikipedia

Isothecium myosuroides.label: Isothecium myosuroides
Isothecium myosuroides.description: Isothecium myosuroides, commonly known as tree moss, is a true moss that grows abundantly on both rocks and trees. It is native to Eastern North America. Wikipedia

Jaffueliobryum arsenei.label: Jaffueliobryum arsenei
Jaffueliobryum arsenei.description: Jaffueliobryum arsenei is a species of moss in the Grimmiaceae family. It is endemic to Mexico. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Jamesoniella colorata.label: Jamesoniella colorata
Jamesoniella colorata.description: Jamesoniella colorata is a species of liverwort in the Jungermanniaceae family. It is found in the zone of the Antarctic Convergence. Samples have been found on the Kerguelen islands, Crozet islands, and the Prince Edward islands. Wikipedia

Lepidopilum grevilleanum.label: Lepidopilum grevilleanum
Lepidopilum grevilleanum.description: Lepidopilum grevilleanum is a species of moss in the Daltoniaceae family. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Meesia triquetra.label: Meesia triquetra
Meesia triquetra.description: Threeranked humpmoss, is a moss that occurs all around the northern hemisphere in higher latitudes. Wikipedia

Meesia uliginosa.label: Meesia uliginosa
Meesia uliginosa.description: Broadnerved humpmoss, is a rare moss of the Western U.S. It occurs all around the northern hemisphere in higher latitudes, and in some places is not as rare as in the Western U.S. Wikipedia

Molendoa.label: Molendoa
Molendoa.description:
Molendoa is a genus of moss in family Pottiaceae. It contains the following species
Molendoa ogalalensis, G.L. Smith Wikipedia

Oedipodiella.label: Oedipodiella
Oedipodiella.description: Oedipodiella is a genus of moss in the family Gigaspermaceae; it contains the single species Oedipodiella australis. This species is restricted to wooded areas of open grassland in South Africa, although a variety is reported from Spain. Wikipedia

Pallaviciniaceae.label: Pallaviciniaceae
Pallaviciniaceae.description: Pallaviciniaceae is a widely distributed family of liverworts in the order Metzgeriales. All species are thallose, typically organized as a thick central costa, each side with a broad wing of tissue one cell in thickness. All species are dioicous. Wikipedia

Porella.label: Porella
Porella.description: Porella is a large, common, and widespread genus of liverworts in order Jungermanniales. It is a member of the family Porellaceae within that order. There are more than 100 species known, most of them from East Asia. Wikipedia

Tetrodontium brownianum.label: Tetrodontium brownianum
Tetrodontium brownianum.description: Tetrodontium brownianum, is a species of moss commonly known as Brown's Tetrodontium Moss or Four-tooth Moss. It is widely distributed. Wikipedia

Andreaea regularis.label: Andreaea regularis
Andreaea regularis.description: Andreaea regularis is a species of moss that grows in Antarctica and on the South Shetland Islands. Wikipedia

Zygodon.label: Zygodon
Zygodon.description: Zygodon is a genus of moss in family Orthotrichaceae. Wikipedia

Andreaeobryum.label: Andreaeobryum
Andreaeobryum.description: Andreaeobryum is a genus of moss with a single species Andreaeobryum macrosporum, endemic to Alaska and western Canada. The genus is placed as a separate family, order and class among the mosses. Wikipedia
